remarks: Given two distinct surreals with the same birthday, there is an older surreal lying between the two of them.  Alling's axiom (SD). (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 16-Jun-2011.)
statement:
nodense $p |- ( ( ( A e. No /\ B e. No ) /\ ( ( bday ` A ) = ( bday ` B ) /\ A <s B ) ) -> E. x e. No ( ( bday ` x ) e. ( bday ` A ) /\ A <s x /\ x <s B ) ) $.
$d A x $.
$d B x $.
